  "title": "LOOKING FOR CONSTRUCTION MANAGER",
  "description": "<ul><li>Develop and implement detailed construction plans, schedules, and budgets to ensure timely and cost-effective delivery of all project milestones.</li><li>Coordinate and manage all phases of infrastructure development, including roads, bridges, water supply, sewerage systems, drainage, culverts, landscape, WTP, STP, CETP, ICT components</li><li>Supervise and guide multidisciplinary teams, including engineers, site supervisors, and subcontractors.</li><li>Ensure smooth communication among stakeholders such as architects, contractors, vendors, and government authorities.</li><li>Monitor the quality of construction activities and ensure strict compliance with safety, environmental, and regulatory standards.</li><li>Conduct routine site inspections and provide solutions for any technical or structural challenges.</li><li>Ensure optimal allocation of manpower, materials, and equipment by the contractor to meet project timelines</li><li>Ensure the project complies with local building codes and standards, along with the timely permits, as required</li><li>Maintain accurate project documentation, including progress reports, construction drawings, and as-built plans</li></ul>",
